        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 5:06PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Smackover to near Cotton Valley,
or extending from near Smackover to 16 miles south of Springhill,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Dorado, Magnolia, Springhill, Smackover, Waldo, Norphlet,
McNeil, Haynesville, Cullen, Cotton Valley, Sarepta, Taylor,
Emerson, Shongaloo, Atlanta, Macedonia, Village, Smithland, Mount
Holly and Bussey.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
